Package dev.blocky.library.jda.entities Description

Root package of the JDA-Common entities.
From here you can navigate to the Discord entities.
  • Direct message channel
    Represents the connection used for direct messaging.
  • Guild member
    Represents a guild-specific user.
  • Guild message channel
    Represents a Discord channel that can have messages and files sent to it.
  • Guild news channel
    Represents standard guild message channel that are news channels. The Discord client may refer to these as announcement channels. Members can subscribe channels in their own guilds to receive messages cross-posted from this channel. This is referred to as following this channel. Messages sent in this channel can be cross-posted, at which point they will be sent (via webhook) to all subscribed channels.
  • Guild target member
    Represents the member instance for the target user.
  • Guild text channel
    Represents a Discord text guild channel.
  • Guild thread channel
    Represents private/public/news Discord thread channel.
  • Guild thread member
    Represents a member, who joined a thread channel.
  • Self member
    Represents the self member (aka. the bot itself) of a specific guild.
